name: CustomObjectDataSingleInstance-CustomObjects-POST-postCustomObjects
description: [Custom Object Data (single-instance)] POST /customObjects/{customObjectAlias} — Create a new, or update an existing instance of a custom object.

schema.name: customObjectAlias
schema.description: The web service alias of the custom object. To determine the web service alias of the custom object definition in Workday, run the View Custom Object task.

schema.name: updateIfExists
schema.description: If true, updates the custom object instance if it exists. If false, returns an error if the object exists. The default is false. If the object does not exist, a new object is created regardless of this setting.

schema.name: bulk
schema.description: If true, creates or updates the specified array of custom object instances in the request body. If false, creates the specified custom object instance (without an array). The default is false.

schema.name: requestBody
schema.description: The custom object instance to be persisted. If bulk=true, specify a JSON array containing the custom object instances, with a maximum of 100. If bulk=false (default), specify a JSON object.

name: CustomObjectDataSingleInstance-CustomObjects-GET-getCustomObjects
description: [Custom Object Data (single-instance)] GET /customObjects/{customObjectAlias}/{customObjectID} — Retrieves a custom object instance.

schema.name: customObjectAlias
schema.description: The web service alias of the custom object. To determine the web service alias of the custom object definition in Workday, run the View Custom Object task.

schema.name: customObjectID
schema.description: The Workday ID of the extended Workday object instance or the custom object instance.

name: CustomObjectDataSingleInstance-CustomObjects-PUT-putCustomObjects
description: [Custom Object Data (single-instance)] PUT /customObjects/{customObjectAlias}/{customObjectID} — Updates  a custom object instance.

schema.name: customObjectAlias
schema.description: The web service alias of the custom object. To determine the web service alias of the custom object definition in Workday, run the View Custom Object task.

schema.name: customObjectID
schema.description: The Workday ID of the extended Workday object instance or the custom object instance.

schema.name: requestBody
schema.description: The custom object fields to be updated.

name: CustomObjectDataSingleInstance-CustomObjects-DELETE-deleteCustomObjects
description: [Custom Object Data (single-instance)] DELETE /customObjects/{customObjectAlias}/{customObjectID} — Deletes a custom object instance.

schema.name: customObjectAlias
schema.description: The web service alias of the custom object. To determine the web service alias of the custom object definition in Workday, run the View Custom Object task.

schema.name: customObjectID
schema.description: The Workday ID of the extended Workday object instance or the custom object instance.
